#Creating Docker image

1) Create a Dockerfile in the root of your Spring Boot project. This file will contain the instructions for building the Docker image.

2) Build the image by running this command
    -   docker build -t your-image-name .

3) Verify that the image is created by running
    -   docker images

4) Run your image by running  (Where the first 8080 is the local port and the second 8080 is the container port)
    -   docker run -p 8080:8080 your-image-name